  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for xen",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for xen fixes the following issues:\n\nSecurity issue fixed:\n\n- CVE-2020-28368: Fixed the Intel RAPL sidechannel attack, aka PLATYPUS attack, aka XSA-351 (bsc#1178591).\n\nNon-security issues fixed:\n\n- Updated to Xen 4.12.4 bug fix release (bsc#1027519).\n- Fixed a panic during MSI cleanup on AMD hardware (bsc#1027519).\n- Adjusted help for --max_iters, default is 5 (bsc#1177950).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
